images.title: Nigel Thompson / Holme Moor railway station (site), Yorkshire
images.caption: Holme Moor railway station (site). Actually located in Holme-(up)on-Spalding-Moor village, the station always carried the abbreviated name. Believed to have opened in 1848 by the North Eastern Railway on the line from Market Weighton to Selby, this station closed to passengers in 1954 and completely in 1965. Former forecourt.

description: This large village in the East Riding of Yorkshire is located just to the west of Market Weighton. This circular walk from the village takes you north to explore the Bubwith Rail Trail. Here you can visit the site of the old Holme-on-Spalding-Moor rail station and enjoy easy walks along the now disused railway line. You can extend the walk by continuing west to visit the neighbouring village of Bubwith. Following the trail east will take you towards Market Weighton where you can enjoy easy waterside walks along the Market Weighton Canal .
